.TH "read_i2c_reg" 9 "read_i2c_reg" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
read_i2c_reg \- reads an internal i2c register
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" read_i2c_reg
.BI "(void __iomem *addr "  ","
.BI "u8 index "  ","
.BI "u8 *data "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "addr" 12
dt3155 mmio base address
.IP "index" 12
index (internal address) of register to read
.IP "data" 12
pointer to byte the read data will be placed in
.SH "RETURN"
zero on success or error code
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function starts reading the specified (by index) register
and busy waits for the process to finish. The result is placed
in a byte pointed by data.
